label: p
comment:
Active power at the point of common coupling. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution in the case a simplified power flow model is used.

label: targetUdc
comment: Target value for DC voltage magnitude. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: targetPpcc
comment: Real power injection target in AC grid, at point of common coupling.  Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

label: q
comment:
Reactive power at the point of common coupling. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution in the case a simplified power flow model is used.

label: connected
comment:
The connected status is related to a bus-branch model and the topological node to terminal relation.  True implies the terminal is connected to the related topological node and false implies it is not. 
In a bus-branch model, the connected status is used to tell if equipment is disconnected without having to change the connectivity described by the topological node to terminal relation. A valid case is that conducting equipment can be connected in one end and open in the other. In particular for an AC line segment, where the reactive line charging can be significant, this is a relevant case.

label: value
comment: Value of active power limit. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: value
comment: The apparent power limit. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: asynchronousMachineType
comment: Indicates the type of Asynchronous Machine (motor or generator).

label: storedE
comment: Amount of energy currently stored. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero and lower than BatteryUnit.ratedE.

label: batteryState
comment: The current state of the battery (charging, full, etc.).

label: pTolerance
comment: Active power net interchange tolerance. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: netInterchange
comment: The specified positive net interchange into the control area, i.e. positive sign means flow into the area.

label: operatingMode
comment: Indicates whether the DC pole is operating as an inverter or as a rectifier. It is converter’s control variable used in power flow.

label: pPccControl
comment: Kind of active power control.

label: targetIdc
comment: DC current target value. It is converter’s control variable used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: targetGamma
comment: Target extinction angle. It is converter’s control variable used in power flow. It is only applicable for inverter if continuous tap changer control is used. Allowed values are within the range minGamma<=targetGamma<=maxGamma. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: targetAlpha
comment: Target firing angle. It is converter’s control variable used in power flow. It is only applicable for rectifier if continuous tap changer control is used. Allowed values are within the range minAlpha<=targetAlpha<=maxAlpha. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: value
comment: Limit on current flow. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: q
comment:
Reactive power of the load. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
For voltage dependent loads the value is at rated voltage.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

label: p
comment:
Active power of the load. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
For voltage dependent loads the value is at rated voltage.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

label: activePower
comment:
High voltage source active injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for steady state solutions.

label: reactivePower
comment:
High voltage source reactive injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for steady state solutions.

label: voltageAngle
comment: Phase angle of a-phase open circuit used when voltage characteristics need to be imposed at the node associated with the terminal of the energy source, such as when voltages and angles from the transmission level are used as input to the distribution network. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: voltageMagnitude
comment: Phase-to-phase open circuit voltage magnitude used when voltage characteristics need to be imposed at the node associated with the terminal of the energy source, such as when voltages and angles from the transmission level are used as input to the distribution network. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: inService
comment: Specifies the availability of the equipment. True means the equipment is available for topology processing, which determines if the equipment is energized or not. False means that the equipment is treated by network applications as if it is not in the model.

label: p
comment:
Equivalent active power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for steady state solutions.

label: regulationTarget
comment: The target voltage for voltage regulation. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: q
comment:
Equivalent reactive power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for steady state solutions.

label: regulationStatus
comment: Specifies the regulation status of the EquivalentInjection.  True is regulating.  False is not regulating.

label: referencePriority
comment: Priority of unit for use as powerflow voltage phase angle reference bus selection. 0 = don t care (default) 1 = highest priority. 2 is less than 1 and so on.

label: p
comment:
Active power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for steady state solutions.

label: q
comment:
Reactive power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for steady state solutions.

label: normalPF
comment: Generating unit economic participation factor.  The sum of the participation factors across generating units does not have to sum to one.  It is used for representing distributed slack participation factor. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: q
comment:
Reactive power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

label: p
comment:
Active power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

label: controlEnabled
comment: Specifies the regulation status of the equipment.  True is regulating, false is not regulating.

label: discrete
comment: The regulation is performed in a discrete mode. This applies to equipment with discrete controls, e.g. tap changers and shunt compensators.

label: targetValueUnitMultiplier
comment: Specify the multiplier for used for the targetValue.

label: targetValue
comment: The target value specified for case input.   This value can be used for the target value without the use of schedules. The value has the units appropriate to the mode attribute.

label: maxAllowedTargetValue
comment: Maximum allowed target value (RegulatingControl.targetValue).

label: targetDeadband
comment:
This is a deadband used with discrete control to avoid excessive update of controls like tap changers and shunt compensator banks while regulating.  The units of those appropriate for the mode. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero. If RegulatingControl.discrete is set to "false", the RegulatingControl.targetDeadband is to be ignored.
Note that for instance, if the targetValue is 100 kV and the targetDeadband is 2 kV the range is from 99 to 101 kV.

label: minAllowedTargetValue
comment: Minimum allowed target value (RegulatingControl.targetValue).

label: enabled
comment: The flag tells if regulation is enabled.

label: q
comment:
Reactive power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

label: p
comment:
Active power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

label: sections
comment:
Shunt compensator sections in use. Starting value for steady state solution. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero. Non integer values are allowed to support continuous variables. The reasons for continuous value are to support study cases where no discrete shunt compensators has yet been designed, a solutions where a narrow voltage band force the sections to oscillate or accommodate for a continuous solution as input. 
For LinearShuntConpensator the value shall be between zero and ShuntCompensator.maximumSections. At value zero the shunt compensator conductance and admittance is zero. Linear interpolation of conductance and admittance between the previous and next integer section is applied in case of non-integer values.
For NonlinearShuntCompensator-s shall only be set to one of the NonlinearShuntCompenstorPoint.sectionNumber. There is no interpolation between NonlinearShuntCompenstorPoint-s.

label: q
comment:
Reactive power injection. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.
Starting value for a steady state solution.

label: locked
comment:
If true, the switch is locked. The resulting switch state is a combination of locked and Switch.open attributes as follows:
  • locked=true and Switch.open=true. The resulting state is open and locked;
  • locked=false and Switch.open=true. The resulting state is open;
  • locked=false and Switch.open=false. The resulting state is closed.

label: open
comment: The attribute tells if the switch is considered open when used as input to topology processing.

label: operatingMode
comment: Current mode of operation.

label: referencePriority
comment: Priority of unit for use as powerflow voltage phase angle reference bus selection. 0 = don t care (default) 1 = highest priority. 2 is less than 1 and so on.

label: controlEnabled
comment: Specifies the regulation status of the equipment.  True is regulating, false is not regulating.

label: step
comment:
Tap changer position.
Starting step for a steady state solution. Non integer values are allowed to support continuous tap variables. The reasons for continuous value are to support study cases where no discrete tap changer has yet been designed, a solution where a narrow voltage band forces the tap step to oscillate or to accommodate for a continuous solution as input.
The attribute shall be equal to or greater than lowStep and equal to or less than highStep.

label: value
comment: Limit on voltage. High or low limit nature of the limit depends upon the properties of the operational limit type. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: qPccControl
comment: Kind of reactive power control.

label: droop
comment: Droop constant. The pu value is obtained as D [kV/MW] x Sb / Ubdc. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: droopCompensation
comment: Compensation constant. Used to compensate for voltage drop when controlling voltage at a distant bus. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: targetQpcc
comment: Reactive power injection target in AC grid, at point of common coupling.  Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

label: targetPowerFactorPcc
comment: Power factor target at the AC side, at point of common coupling. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: qShare
comment: Reactive power sharing factor among parallel converters on Uac control. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: pPccControl
comment: Kind of control of real power and/or DC voltage.

label: targetUpcc
comment: Voltage target in AC grid, at point of common coupling. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: targetPWMfactor
comment: Magnitude of pulse-modulation factor. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: targetPhasePcc
comment: Phase target at AC side, at point of common coupling. The attribute shall be a positive value.
